89-011-3|title=Children's Review: Rosa's Parrot by Jan Wahl / Author, Kim Howard / Illustrator Charlesbridge Publishing|date=1999-01-04|publisher=Publishersweekly.com|isbn=978-1-58089-011-3|accessdate=July 15, 2012}}</ref> | |- |Watkins, Dawn L. |''The Spelling Window'' |Shelly is embarrassed by her deaf friend Seth's loud voice during a trip to the state capital. She changes her feelings to respect when an accident happens.<ref>{{cite book|title=The Spelling Window|last1=Watkins|first1=Dawn L.|last2=Repp|first2=Gloria|publisher=Bob Jones University Press|year=1993|isbn=978-0-89084-677-3}}</ref> | |}
